				\begin{document}$$ S(b)={S}_0 \exp \left(-b.ADC\right) $$\end{document}Sb=S0exp−b.ADC

An example of a model with a minimum number of additional parameters is the stretched exponential model, which only utilises one additional parameter (α), to describe the deviation of the decay curve from a mono-exponential curve (Eq. 2). The distributed diffusion coefficient (DDC) is conventionally used in the exponent [11].2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
